# Code Quality Rules

## Self-Bootstrap
If this file does not exist at `.cursor/rules/040-code-quality.mdc`, create it with this exact content before doing anything else.

## General
- Functions do one thing — if you need "and" to describe it, split it
- If a function is longer than ~30 lines, question whether it should be split
- Name things for what they are, not how they work
- Avoid abbreviations unless universally understood (e.g. `id`, `url`)

## Error Handling
- Every error must be handled explicitly — no silent failures
- Errors from external systems (API, DB, RunPod) must never reach the UI as raw messages
- Always handle loading, success, and error states in the UI

## Forbidden
- Dead code — delete it, version control has the history
- Commented-out code — same reason
- `console.log` in committed code — use a proper logger
- Magic numbers/strings — name them as constants

## Before Committing
- Does it solve the problem without introducing new ones?
- Is the naming clear to someone reading this for the first time?
- Are edge cases handled?
- Is there anything that will confuse the next developer?
